data.title: Jamie Lynn Spears' baby daddy Casey Aldridge 'arrested with prescription drugs while passed out'
data.meta_description: Aldridge, 29, who shares a 10-year-old daughter named Maddie with Jamie Lynn Spears, was passed out behind the wheel of the vehicle at the time police checked on him
data.text:
Jamie Lynn Spears' baby daddy Casey Aldridge was arrested after police found Oxycodone, Lorazepam, Xanax and drug paraphernalia on him upon finding him passed out in a vehicle parked alongside the road in Natchez, Mississippi.

Aldridge, 29, who shares a 10-year-old daughter named Maddie Aldridge with Britney Spears' younger sister Jamie Lynn, 27, was passed out behind the wheel of the vehicle at the time police checked on him, TMZ reported Tuesday citing police records.

He was hospitalized in the wake of the incident, which occurred last week, and was arrested in connection with drug possession when he awoke, the outlet reported.

It's not his first brush with the law, as he was arrested in May of 2016 in Amite County, Mississippi in connection with driving under the influence, reckless driving and possession of paraphernalia, Radar reported; he subsequently served a year's probation after he was found guilty of the charges.

Aldridge was in the limelight in 2007 when Jamie Lynn was 16 when she became pregnant with Maddie at time she was the lead actress on the Nickelodeon series Zoey 101. The pair, who were engaged for a time, welcomed Maddie June 19, 2008.

Spears last April welcomed her second daughter, Ivey Joan, with her husband of nearly five years, Jamie Watson.

Aldridge is also father to a four-year-old daughter named Skylar Brooke with ex-wife April Watson. He finalized his divorce from Watson last June, Radar reported.

Jamie Lynn made headlines last month when she said on Instagram that Zoey 101 did not wrap up in 2008 because of her pregnancy, but rather because her contractual obligations had ended.

She made the revelation in commemorating the 14th anniversary of the program, posting a shot from the show's theme, with the caption, 'Are you ready? 14 years later...still a jam...'' adding the hashtags, #itdidNOTendbecauseofpregnancy and #contractwasfinished.

She added in response to a user's question, 'I went home to finish high school and was going to pursue movies.'
